  <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Results come back immediately: total calories burned (kcal), the MET value for that specific combination, calories per minute, speed confirmation, and distance covered during the session.
  </p>
  <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6 shadow-sm">
    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed"><span class="font-semibold text-slate-800">Example:</span> 70 kg, male, age 30, speed 8 km/h, incline 1%, duration 30 minutes → around 280–300 kcal, MET roughly 8.3.</p>
  </div>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-800 mt-6 mb-2">Tab 2: Pace &amp; Distance</h3>
  <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
    Nothing to do with calories here — this tab handles the running math. Enter speed and duration, hit Calculate, and get back total distance covered, pace per kilometer or mile, and a split table. Up to 20 full splits appear row by row, with a partial split row at the bottom if there's a remaining fraction of distance. If training toward a race and working backward from a goal pace, this tab shows exactly what treadmill speed to set and what each split should clock.
